net.casper.data.model

Class CTypes

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.casper.data.model.CTypes
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CDataConverter

    public class CTypes
extends Object
implements Serializable
    This class provides the various data types supported in data conversion. The reason all of the data types are created as static integers is an optimization to allow for *FAST* switching. The alternative to this approach to is utilize the "instanceof" operation to determine type equality which is known to be performance intensive, in large quantities. Since type conversion is used frequently, the optimization makes sense.
    Since:
    1.0
    Version:
    $Revision: 111 $
    Author:
